reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Reliable and Durable Charging Cable for Apple Devices
reviews.reviewText: I've been using the AmazonBasics USB-A to Lightning Charger Cable for several months now, and I'm more than satisfied with its performance. I primarily use it to charge my iPhone 13 Pro Max and my company-issued iPhone X.One of the standout features of this cable is its build quality. The connectors and wires feel sturdy and well-made, eliminating that cheap and flimsy sensation often associated with other charging cables. The nylon braided cord adds an extra layer of durability, making it resistant to wear and tear.I primarily use this cable in my office, where it has become an essential part of my setup. The 6-foot length provides ample reach, allowing me to comfortably use my devices while they charge. The rose gold color adds a touch of elegance, making it visually appealing as well.The connection performance is excellent, and I've experienced no issues with the cable. It connects seamlessly to my Apple devices, and the charging speed is on par with Apple's original cables. I appreciate the MFi certification, ensuring compatibility and reliability with Apple products.One of the most impressive aspects is that after several months of regular use, I have encountered no problems with the cable. It has proven to be a durable and long-lasting solution for my charging needs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I love this charger!!
reviews.reviewText: I bought a 2 pack 6ft pack. I love the chargers so much. They’re double the length (the charger included with an iPhone is 3ft), it includes two, they’re braided for better durability, and there are 2 of them!! For reference, an apple charger that is 3ft not braided is $20 (the same price for this pack). These will last you so so so long. They’re also from a reputable company (amazon), so you’ll get great support and help you may need. I used to have this 5 pack of chargers for 8 bucks. Yes it seemed like a great deal, but the quality was horrible. They stopped after a week. 4 of them did. I didn’t use the 5th one because I knew how it would go. Just spend a bit more money and get this. It’ll last you years if you treat it right.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Reliable Charging on the Go: Amazon Basics USB-A to Lightning Cable
reviews.reviewText: Disclaimer: Tested during Uber Eats deliveries to ensure uninterrupted connectivity.As an Uber driver, having a reliable charging cable is essential to meet the demands of a busy day on the road. The Amazon Basics USB-A to Lightning Charger Cable has proven invaluable companion. Here's why I'm impressed:1. MFi Certified Assurance:Knowing that this cable is MFi certified provides peace of mind. It guarantees quality and compatibility, ensuring my devices charge safely and efficiently.2. Durable and Tangle-Free:The nylon braided cord is a game-changer. It not only adds durability, preventing fraying and wear, but it also resists tangling. No more untangling knots before plugging in!3. Perfect Length for Convenience:This cable allows passengers to comfortably charge their devices at just the right length without any awkward stretching or limited mobility. It strikes a balance between accessibility and avoiding clutter.4. Swift Charging Speeds:The charging speed is impressive. It delivers a fast and consistent charge, crucial to ensure my phone is always ready for navigation and communication with passengers.5. Compatibility Across Devices:This cable has proven versatile whether it's an iPhone, iPad, or other Lightning-compatible device. It meets the charging needs of a wide range of passengers.6. Tangle-Free Storage:When not in use, the cable coils neatly and stays tangle-free. This makes for efficient storage in my car, so it's always within reach when needed.7. Dependable in All Conditions:Rain or shine, this cable has held up under various weather conditions. I've never experienced connectivity issues, even during heavy rain or extreme temperatures.

The Amazon Basics Nylon USB-A to Lightning Cable impressed me with its MFi certification, ensuring compatibility and reliability with Apple devices. The 6-ft length provides flexibility, and the dark gray nylon exterior adds durability. Fast and efficient charging make it a reliable choice for iPhone and iPad users.
